This paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category as it deals with the concept of incentive ratio, which is a measure of strategic behaviour in games. It may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses the computational challenges involved in manipulating equilibria. Additionally, it could be classified under Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as these fields often involve game-theoretic models. Finally, it could be classified under the Economics and Computation (cs.EC) sub-category as it deals with exchange markets and utility gains.
